{
  "texts": [
    "(3) Models with attention mechanisms, such as Informer, are more likely to improve prediction performance when sentiment data is added as input, which demonstrates the strength of selfattention mechanisms in capturing intercompany relationships, which are crucial for understanding the influence of related firms on stock prices.",
    "This research has certain limitations.",
    "The API used to collect news data is limited to publicly listed companies, with a bias toward American companies, resulting in less comprehensive coverage for other regions.",
    "To address this, alternative data sources will be explored in future work.Another limitation lies in the NER process used to extract companies mentioned in financial news.",
    "Although NER effectively identifies potential companies, the final selection of relevant companies is performed manually on the basis of frequency, which introduces subjectivity and may limit scalability, especially for large datasets."
  ]
}